Unfortunately, Chairman Mao agreed with the Soviet Union. He wanted to build new industrial centers in Beijing. [p]
After he read about Liang's proposal, he said: "There is a professor who wants to kick us out of Beijing. I think, when I am looking down from Tiananmen again, I want to see a lot of Chimneys: a highly developed City"[p]
Therefore, Liang's proposal was completely abandoned. The destruction of ancient architecture and city walls began. The new industrial centers also lead to severe pollution in the future. [p]
